```python

    'value': 0.4,
    'next_plays': {'predicted_opponent_next_play': 'paper', 'my_next_play': 'scissors'}
}

Based on the interaction history, I notice that my opponent has played scissors frequently, especially in recent rounds. In rounds 285-291, my opponent played scissors in every round, and I played rock in every round, earning a reward of 3 each time. This suggests that my opponent may be playing a Dynamic Scissors-biased policy with reaction-based responses and weakness against rock.
